reviews.text: I graduated from here in 2009 in Humanities. I went and continued my studies in UCD in 2016 and I preferred Carlow College. The Carlow College lecturers and staff were top notch. They were friendly and helpful. Most knew the students names and the high quality lectures had a relaxed and personal touch. I wasn't mad about living in Carlow but the College was decent.
Very nice place the fountain looks amazing.
Small town. But full of characters.
Well maintained
Dirty
Excellent little quick stop right in the middle of town. Not much to do besides read a plaque or twoand take a walk around the outside
Nice place to visit and to read the plaques and learn the history of how it came to be and why it's protected. Worth the stop over and impactfull to say the least.
Well worth a visit when in carlow

The limited wall and towers have  been cared for with walkway and garden makes pleasant spot in town. A shame an early restoration attempt removed a lot and we didn't find any historical information from before.
Fun place to visit.

This old house is an interesting place to visit. In recent times the walled gardens have been renovated and there are a series of short walks in and around the property.

There is free car parking on site along with a cafe. For those with limited mobility this would be a good place to go.

Up until recently you could go inside the ruins of the house but now closed off for renovations. How long this will be, will be anyone’s guess.
The most gorgeous castle! We walked around for ages taking pictures and such at sunset... It was very quiet and beautiful!

Great place to visit with the family and pets. There is shops in the summer but closed in the winter. The walled gardens are nice to walk on as well. Great literature all around to tell of the past and how the grounds came to be as they are now.

Lovely spot for a walk around some beautifully kept grounds. 
Always worth stopping by!
Amazing old castle, perfect for short relaxing Sunday walk.
Great Park, kids love going there, especially love walking down looking at the small boats and feeding the swans
Great pleace to relax when its nice outside. Great play area for kids however sometines full of empy cans and bottles on a weekend morning
Perfect park.
Great fun run
Peaceful
Great place to visit. Love looking at all the art
Fantastic place to visit. Very interesting and informative. Child friendly and the staff are helpful too.
Nice little museum. Wouldn't go there second time.

Very enjoyable, particular as there is such a mix of exhibits. Very much something for everyone.

The museum is split over 3 floors, so it may be a little larger than one's initial impression.
Beautiful museum and free. Lots to see and learn for all ages

I graduated from here in 2009 in Humanities. I went and continued my studies in UCD in 2016 and I preferred Carlow College. The Carlow College lecturers and staff were top notch. They were friendly and helpful. Most knew the students names and the high quality lectures had a relaxed and personal touch. I wasn't mad about living in Carlow but the College was decent.

Today's trip to Shaws Department Store in Carlow was a great experience. The staff were really enjoying the Christmas rush made everyone feel welcome and join in the festive fun. If you have Christmas shopping left to do I would recommend Shaws Department Store in Carlow.
Excellent choice of clothing and prices won't break your heart  😀
Good variety of moderate price designs only fault not one till have to go to each department to pay .I had to go to 3 tills

Nice simple pub food. We stopped off in Carlow at this pub on the way to Dublin. Glad we did. It was lovely simple food and the price wasn't too bad either. We got served promptly and without fuss. The toilet was clean and tidy and even though there was a TV on it wasn't so loud as to drown out conversation as in many pubs. Would recommend it to anyone needing a quick stop off for refreshments and use of the facilities.
Great place for carvery, value for money and a great choice, staff very helpful and friendly. Only  one thing  I'd  say is the carvery finishes too early 3pm. They have a menu after 3pm.

New management has done an amazing job taking this location to the next level.  Service is top notch and the food quality has improved exponentially!  Speed of service is noticably faster.  Definitely will be having more quick lunches here in the near future!
Agree! Food quality has gotten so much better since the old owner sold it.
